{
  "stem": "24268.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We tried to make-- with our neighbors, [? maids, ?] and friends, we tried-- my brother always created.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We tried to make shows.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they get together and bake something like this, and play, and sing, and make a show, which they had to pay tickets.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And for this money, we got something to share between the kids.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And mainly, it was-- I even-- when I would play mandolin, whatever one could.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And how we did enjoy it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Well, like I-- like I said, that was-- that's the way we could make the best of it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we go to movie, or the parents took us, because we weren't allowed to go to any movie without escorting.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And books-- we weren't allowed only certain books.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That was always a limit for that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But we had our stories and traditions.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we read-- we read very-- later on, I read very important artists.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Like I used to like good books, like Dickens, and Dumas, and Raymond, and [?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Vassamun ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I hated Tolstoy.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And [INAUDIBLE] is one thing I hated in school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But otherwise, we do enjoy literature.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And my parents always very knowledgeable and otherwise try to teach our children to use as much-- to learn as much as you can.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we had friends, which they were deported.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And some of them tried to copy, [LAUGHS] to be [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we've been very close to each other.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And-- and I would say-- no.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, we did not-- I tried, in the beginning-- we used to have some-- before we bought our home, we lived in an apartment with the Jews and-- practically we'd been the only practically Jew there.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Across the street, we had-- which they'd been very close with my parents.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They're businesspeople also.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
